Police in Polokwane have launched a search party for 11-year-old Lesiba Kenneth Lekoloane from Flora Park Comprehensive Primary School who allegedly went missing last Friday.
Provincial Police Spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe informed that the boy, who is from Ga-Mashashane, was allegedly last seen by the scholar transport driver who had dropped him off at school last Friday morning.
The Police searched for the learner at friends and relatives but could not be located. He was wearing Flora Park Comprehensive Primary School uniform at the time of his disappearance.
Anyone with information can contact the investigating officer Peter Mangakeng on 082 878 8525 or 071 144 9179 or report to the nearest Police station.
